"title": "7429: Sabbath, in OT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7429",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The Sabbath of rest is grounded in God's work of creation. Observance of a Sabbath day is distinctive of the people of God.</p>\n<h2>The Sabbath grounded in creation itself</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:3\">GEN 2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:24\">PSA 118:24</a></p>\n<h2>The purpose of the Sabbath</h2>\n<h3>To remember God's work in creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:8-Exod20:11\">EXO 20:8–20:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:2\">GEN 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:2\">EXO 35:2</a></p>\n<h3>To remember the exodus</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:12-Deut5:15\">DEU 5:12–5:15</a></strong> <em>The idea of rest relates the concept of the Sabbath to the ultimate conquest of Canaan under David and to the return from exile.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:4\">GEN 8:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:1\">2SA 7:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:11\">2SA 7:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:10-Ps95:11\">PSA 95:10–95:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:9\">HEB 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:13\">REV 14:13</a></p>\n<h3>To be a sign of the relationship between Israel and God and to give refreshment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:17\">EXO 31:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:12-Deut5:14\">DEU 5:12–5:14</a></p>\n<h2>The Law required the Sabbath to be a holy day free from work</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:3\">LEV 23:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:21\">EXO 34:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:3\">EXO 35:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:38\">LEV 23:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:2\">ISA 56:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:13\">ISA 58:13</a></p>\n<h2>The Sabbath was linked with celebration of the New Moon</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:23\">2KI 4:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:13\">ISA 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:3\">EZK 46:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:11\">HOS 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:5\">AMO 8:5</a></p>\n<h2>Abuses of the Sabbath</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:27-Exod16:28\">EXO 16:27–16:28</a> <em>gathering manna</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:32\">NUM 15:32</a> <em>gathering wood</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:15-Neh13:18\">NEH 13:15–13:18</a> <em>doing ordinary work</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:31\">NEH 10:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:5\">AMO 8:5</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:21\">JER 17:21</a> <em>carrying loads</em></p>\n<h2>Punishments for infringing the Sabbath law</h2>\n<h3>The death penalty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:14\">EXO 31:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:35\">NUM 15:35</a></p>\n<h3>Disaster for Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:27\">JER 17:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:13\">EZK 20:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:8\">EZK 22:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:15\">EZK 22:15</a></p>\n<h2>Sacrifices to be offered on the Sabbath</h2>\n<h3>Bread</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:8\">LEV 24:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:32\">1CH 9:32</a></p>\n<h3>Burnt offerings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:9-Num28:10\">NUM 28:9–28:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:31\">1CH 23:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:4\">2CH 2:4</a></p>\n<h3>Other offerings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:4\">EZK 46:4</a></p>",
